{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ca14fbe1-cffc-4b9b-b110-062126a0ae83","content":"To migrate your NUnit project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. **Replace packages** in your `.csproj`:\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n   - Remove `NUnit3TestAdapter`\n   - Add `NUnit.Runner` (≥ 4.3.0) — this is the MTP-native runner for NUnit\n\n2. **Add the MTP property** to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or directly:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet run --project YourTests.csproj\n   ```\n\n4. **Optional** — if you use extensions (e.g., code coverage, TRX reports), add their MTP equivalents:\n   - `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n   - `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n\nThe `NUnit.Runner` package bundles the MTP harness and NUnit adapter together, replacing both `NUnit3TestAdapter` and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a52700b4-686b-4796-b15f-cfb5599efd3f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a general knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure - I don't need to look at any files since this is a guidance question, not a code change request.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":388,"requestId":"BC51:DC2FD:1C9FB04:1FAA019:69FA8F72"},"id":"7e6bc08c-fe2d-4c02-98e8-08e2e963e4fb","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:46:51.343Z","parentId":"ae6d7ea1-96b5-4a4c-96d6-f925d7755642"}
